reviewText: This poorly crafted documentary is like a parody of itself. It loosely explores possible correlations between The Book of Revelations and a coming apocalypse based on things like recent weather patterns, economic conditions, etc. If you are okay with zero science then this might be for you. The host repeatedly asks people such thought provoking questions as, "If millions of people just disappeared without a trace, what do you think would be the cause of it?" Hmmm... LOL.

reviewText: This documentary does point out some events that are taken place before our eyes. The makers of this film allows the viewer to draw to their own thinking if the events are something that is meaningful, or just somthing that is happening.I think this is a have to see it for yourself documentary. After you see this documentary, you will start looking at the news alot different.

reviewText: The film tries to make the point that we are oblivious to the coming End Days by interviewing revelers at Mardi Gras in New Orleans.  Amateurish cinematography and inane, repetitive questioning  that makes you want to fling something at the screen.  Nothing new brought to the table.  No intelligent discussion.  I don't even recommend it as a time-waster.

reviewText: This DVD is poorly filmed and produced. I like the subject matter but the interviews were horrible. The people in the interview barely had enough sense to "get out of the rain." I am very disappointed. Warning! Do not purchase this DVD.
